<!--
  Info.plist additions required for the menu-bar-only app.
  Merge these keys into the project's auto-generated Info.plist via Xcode
  target settings (Target → Info → Custom macOS Application Target
  Properties), or paste them into the file if you have it broken out.

  LSUIElement = true: removes the dock icon and prevents the app from
  appearing in the Cmd-Tab switcher. Standard menu-bar-utility pattern
  (Bartender, Rectangle, Hidden Bar all use this).

  CFBundleDisplayName: shows "Cloud to Ground AI" in macOS UI surfaces.

  NSHumanReadableCopyright: small thing but App Store will ask for it
  eventually.

  NSAppTransportSecurity > NSAllowsLocalNetworking: REQUIRED for the
  BridgeProbe.probeOllama() URLSession call to http://localhost:11434.
  Without this, App Transport Security silently blocks plain HTTP to
  localhost and the probe falls through to "Not installed". This is the
  narrowest exception possible — it allows HTTP only to local addresses,
  not arbitrary HTTP destinations. Confirmed via diagnostic 2026-06-29.
-->

<key>LSUIElement</key>
<true/>

<key>CFBundleDisplayName</key>
<string>Cloud to Ground AI</string>

<key>CFBundleName</key>
<string>Cloud to Ground AI</string>

<key>NSHumanReadableCopyright</key>
<string>Copyright © 2026 Carlano Technology Solutions LLC. Apache-2.0 licensed.</string>

<key>NSAppTransportSecurity</key>
<dict>
    <key>NSAllowsLocalNetworking</key>
    <true/>
</dict>

<!--
  SANDBOX / ENTITLEMENTS — see Cloud to Ground AI.entitlements

  New Xcode SwiftUI projects ship with App Sandbox ON. That blocks:
    - Process.run() for shell-outs (pgrep, which, ollama list)
    - URLSession to localhost without network.client entitlement
    - Process enumeration via pgrep -f

  For v0.2 dev builds: App Sandbox is DISABLED in entitlements. This is
  the simplest path to getting the probes working with a Personal-Team
  cert and an unnotarized DMG distribution. ACT-007 will revisit when we
  decide the distribution channel:
    - Notarized DMG outside the App Store → sandbox can stay off
    - Mac App Store → sandbox required + helper-tool XPC pattern for shell
-->
